            <tbody>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>(A)</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>The <ph platform="PXP PxW">UPS</ph>
                        <ph platform="WxW">Inverter</ph>
                        <ph platform="SDC">Charger</ph>
                     </p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Inside the system.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>(B)</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>The network monitoring system</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>The parts of the network monitoring system placed in the low voltage
section<ph platform="SDC"> (for SDC systems the A091 is not
located in the low voltage section.)</ph>.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>A070A102</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>
                        <ph platform="PxW WxW SDC">Controller board</ph>
                        <ph platform="PXP">Controller box</ph>
                     </p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>The <ph platform="PxW WxW SDC">controller board</ph>
                        <ph platform="PXP">controller box</ph> sends information and status changes in the system
to the <ph platform="PXP PxW WxW">communication interface</ph>
                        <ph platform="SDC">external connection board</ph>.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>A076A025A830</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Communication interface</p>
                     <p>External connection board</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Extends the signal from the controller board
and to the smart slot translator.</p>
                     <p>Connects directly
to the network management cards.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row platform="PxW WxW SDC">
                  <entry>
                     <p>A091</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Smart slot translator</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Converts the signal from the controller board to another type of
protocol. Allows for local connection to the NMC.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>A092A842</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Network management card (NMC)</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Offers secure local and/or remote monitoring of Reality systems.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>A093A832</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Options slot</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>An additional slot for an optional second NMC card that can be used
for:<ul>
                           <li>
                              <p>Additional available ports with two NMCs.</p>
                           </li>
                           <li>
                              <p>A second NMC with different settings.</p>
                           </li>
                           <li>
                              <p>Redundant network communication.</p>
                           </li>
                           <li>
                              <p>Two digital inputs.</p>
                           </li>
                        </ul>
                     </p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
